1 products right in the palm of your hand. You can quickly access important key performance indicators for your websites or change the settings for your contract, domains and websites while on the go. And if you want, [&#8230;]</p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://community.1and1.com/1and1-control-panel-ios-android/">1&#038;1 Control Panel for iOS and Android: Manage your Websites, Domains and Settings</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://community.1and1.com">1&amp;1 Community</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:16:"Philipp Bellmann";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:3220:"<p>With the 1&amp;1 Control Panel for iOS and Android, you have all important information and settings for your 1&amp;1 products right in the palm of your hand.</p>\n<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-9678" src="https://community.1and1.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/1and1-control-panel-app-overview_features-Kopie.png" alt="Control Panel for iOS and Android Features" width="7337" height="3413" />\n<p>You can quickly access important key performance indicators for your websites or change the settings for your contract, domains and websites while on the go. And if you want, you can also read interesting posts about web hosting, web design, server technology and SEO topics right in the app.</p>\n<h2>Getting to Know the Home Page</h2>\n<p>The home page gives you direct access to messages, news, statistics and domains. You can use the <strong>menu</strong> to access additional settings.</p>\n<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-9680" src="https://community.1and1.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/1und1-control-center-en_startseite.png" alt="1und1-control-center-en_startseite" width="3834" height="2532" srcset="https://community.1and1.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/1und1-control-center-en_startseite.png 3834w, https://community.1and1.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/1und1-control-center-en_startseite-300x198.png 300w, https://community.1and1.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/1und1-control-center-en_startseite-768x507.png 768w, https://community.1and1.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/1und1-control-center-en_startseite-1024x676.png 1024w" sizes="(max-width: 3834px) 100vw, 3834px" />\n<h2>Discovering All Features</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Easily manage your data and products from your smartphone.</li>\n<li>Keep track of all your invoices.</li>\n<li>Check how <u>1&amp;1 SiteAnalytics</u> is making your websites more successful.</li>\n<li>Register and manage your <u>domains</u>.</li>\n<li>Get answers to your questions in the integrated 1&amp;1 Help Center.</li>\n<li>Knowledge and good ideas make your website unique and successful. That&#8217;s why you can find interesting posts about web hosting and WordPress directly in the 1&amp;1 Control Panel.</li>\n<li>Status updates: We help you by providing background information and offering assistance with technical disruptions.</li>\n<li>Contact us easily and get personalized customer service over the phone: Create your telephone PIN directly in the app.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Downloading 1&amp;1 Control Panel</h2>\n<p>1&amp;1 Control Panel is available free of charge for iOS devices, Android smartphones and tablets with Android 4.4 or later.</p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a class="promo-button" href="https://itunes.apple.com/app/1-1-control-panel/id1080444849?l=en&amp;mt=8">iOS (App Store)</a> and <a class="promo-button" href="https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.oneandone.ciso.mobile.app.android">Android (Google Play)</a></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://community.1and1.com/1and1-control-panel-ios-android/">1&#038;1 Control Panel for iOS and Android: Manage your Websites, Domains and Settings</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://community.1and1.com">1&amp;1 Community</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:65:"https://community.1and1.com/1and1-control-panel-ios-android/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"0";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:4;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:63:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:5:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:59:"Start your eCommerce Website with WordPress and WooCommerce";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:74:"https://community.1and1.com/start-ecommerce-website-wordpress-woocommerce/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:82:"https://community.1and1.com/start-ecommerce-website-wordpress-woocommerce/#respond";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Mon, 12 Dec 2016 10:50:25 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:8:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:9:"eCommerce";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:6:"How-To";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:11:"Information";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:17:"Managed WordPress";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:4;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:4:"WCMS";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:5;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:11:"Web Hosting";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:6;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:9:"WordPress";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:7;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:18:"featured-wordpress";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:35:"https://community.1and1.com/?p=9650";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:723:"<p>39% of all online shops are using WooCommerce already. And with good reason: WooCommerce and WordPress enable you to build powerful and modern online shops and flexible eCommerce websites. WooCommerce combines usability with excellent expandability and perfect WordPress integration. The support by Automattic &#8211; the people behind WordPress &#8211; makes WooCommerce a future-proof platform with reliable long-term support. [&#8230;]</p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://community.1and1.com/start-ecommerce-website-wordpress-woocommerce/">Start your eCommerce Website with WordPress and WooCommerce</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://community.1and1.com">1&amp;1 Community</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:16:"Philipp Bellmann";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:8543:"<p><a href="https://trends.builtwith.com/shop">39% of all online shops</a> are using WooCommerce already. And with good reason:</p>\n<p><strong>WooCommerce and WordPress enable you to build powerful and modern online shops and flexible eCommerce websites. WooCommerce combines usability with excellent expandability and perfect WordPress integration.</strong></p>\n<p>The support by <a href="https://automattic.com/about/">Automattic</a> &#8211; the people behind WordPress &#8211; makes WooCommerce a future-proof platform with reliable long-term support.</p>\n<hr />\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a class="promo-button" href="https://my.1and1.com/APPCenter" target="_blank">Install WooCommerce</a></p>\n<h2>WooCommerce at 1&amp;1</h2>\n<p>When choosing your shop, you are committing to one system for a longer period of time. We like WooCommerce a lot, but there are <a href="https://www.1and1.com/ecommerce-website" target="_blank">alternatives</a> you might want to consider as well.</p>\n<h3>Themes you and your customers will love</h3>\n<p>WooCommerce offer professional, secure and expandable themes for your online shop, company or portfolio. Our wizard will assist you in choosing a secure theme.</p>\n<h3><img class="aligncenter wp-image-9658 size-full" src="https://community.1and1.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/wp-assistent-theme-select-us-01.png" alt="Online Store: Select your Theme" width="2504" height="1346" srcset="https://community.1and1.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/wp-assistent-theme-select-us-01.png 2504w, https://community.1and1.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/wp-assistent-theme-select-us-01-300x161.png 300w, https://community.1and1.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/wp-assistent-theme-select-us-01-768x413.png 768w, https://community.1and1.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/wp-assistent-theme-select-us-01-1024x550.png 1024w" sizes="(max-width: 2504px) 100vw, 2504px" />Simple, international and search-engine-friendly</h3>\n<p>WooCommerce can be installed, adapted for new markets and optimized for search engines (SEO) easily in just a few steps using the 1&amp;1 WP wizard.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>WooCommerce is international: Just like WordPress, WooCommerce offers different locales for all pages and functions of your shop.</li>\n<li>WooCommerce is search-engine-friendly: The combination of WordPress and sophisticated SEO plugins puts all the tools required for effective SEO at your disposal.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>A shop your customers can trust</h3>\n<p>Your online shop is secure. WooCommerce and WordPress are checked and updated on a regular basis to prevent security holes.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Protect your online shop and your customers&#8217; data with SSL encryption.<br />\n<a href="https://community.1and1.com/activate-ssl-for-your-managed-wordpress-websites/">Activate SSL in 1&amp;1 App Center</a></li>\n<li>Combine WooCommerce with professional themes and plugins and receive a system that is extremely secure, despite its widespread distribution.</li>\n<li>Legal clarity for your market: Create legal clarity for your market with out plugin recommendations.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Great user experience, regardless of the products you sell</h3>\n<p>Selling successfully means inspiring your customer from the very start and guiding them to their goal comfortably. That is why WooCommerce employs themes with a modern and tidy interface that provides customers with an easy way to search your products and contents.</p>\n<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-9653" src="https://community.1and1.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/woothemes-storefront-single.gif" alt="woothemes-storefront-single" width="972" height="700" />\n<ul>\n<li>WooCommerce offers support for various business sectors.</li>\n<li>Use dynamic, animated product pages and text effects to highlight selected products.</li>\n<li>Present physical and digital products, services and memberships effectively.</li>\n<li>Offer flexible payment methods for your customers: e.g. pre-orders, subscriptions and single payments.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Image: <a href="http://demo.woothemes.com/storefront/">WooCommerce Theme Demo, Storefront</a></p>\n<h3>Excellent support and documentation</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Regular updates and consistent development.</li>\n<li>The excellent <a href="https://docs.woocommerce.com/">WooCommerce documentation</a> has all the right answers to your questions and problems.</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Install via 1&amp;1 App Center</h2>\n<p>The 1&amp;1 App Center now offers the option to install WordPress with <a href="https://my.1and1.com/APPCenter">WooCommerce free of charge</a>.</p>\n<h3><strong><a href="https://my.1and1.com/APPCenter" target="_blank"><img class="aligncenter wp-image-9657 size-full" src="https://community.1and1.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/wp-assistent-type-select-us-01.png" alt="1&amp;1 App Center: Select Website Type" width="2234" height="1294" srcset="https://community.1and1.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/wp-assistent-type-select-us-01.png 2234w, https://community.1and1.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/wp-assistent-type-select-us-01-300x174.png 300w, https://community.1and1.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/wp-assistent-type-select-us-01-768x445.png 768w, https://community.1and1.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/wp-assistent-type-select-us-01-1024x593.png 1024w" sizes="(max-width: 2234px) 100vw, 2234px" /></a></strong></h3>\n<p>Select the <strong>Online Store</strong> website type in the 1&amp;1 WP wizard after installing WordPress<strong>. </strong>Choose your<strong> WooCommerce theme </strong>and<strong> </strong>expand the range of functions as needed with our recommended <strong>plugins.</strong></p>\n<h3>Getting started with WooCommerce</h3>\n<p>Once installation is complete, the WooCommerce setup wizard will guide you through the basic settings for your online shop. Here you can easily adjust important settings for your location, products and payment methods.</p>\n<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-9654" src="https://community.1and1.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/woocommerce-Get-Started-2-WooCommerce-e1481538438765.png" alt="woocommerce-get-started-2-woocommerce" width="2804" height="2560" srcset="https://community.1and1.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/woocommerce-Get-Started-2-WooCommerce-e1481538438765.png 2804w, https://community.1and1.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/woocommerce-Get-Started-2-WooCommerce-e1481538438765-300x274.png 300w, https://community.1and1.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/woocommerce-Get-Started-2-WooCommerce-e1481538438765-768x701.png 768w, https://community.1and1.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/woocommerce-Get-Started-2-WooCommerce-e1481538438765-1024x935.png 1024w" sizes="(max-width: 2804px) 100vw, 2804px" />\n<p>When the set-up is complete, you will find two new sections in your WordPress admin menu:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>WooCommerce</strong>\n<ul>\n<li>Manage <strong>Orders</strong> and <strong>Vouchers</strong></li>\n<li>Adjust <strong>Settings</strong> for your online shop.</li>\n<li>In the <strong>Reports</strong> section, you will find information on orders, customers and stock management and revenue statistics by date, category or product.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li><strong>Products</strong>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Add product</strong>: Create new products and adjust stock and shipment settings. You can set up cross- and up-selling via linked products.</li>\n<li>Create and edit <strong>Categories </strong>for your online shop. You can use categories to define the order in which your products (categories) are displayed on your website.</li>\n<li>Add <strong>Keywords</strong> and descriptions for products . Keywords will help your customers find related products and can improve recommendations.</li>\n<li>Add <strong>Properties</strong>: Properties allow you to add additional product data such as size or color and use them later in the shop&#8217;s side bar.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>More on WooCommerce</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>The <a href="https://woocommerce.com/features/">features at a glance</a> at woocommerce.com.</li>\n<li>Official <a href="https://docs.woocommerce.com/">Documentation</a>, <a href="https://woocommerce.com/my-account/">Customer service</a>, <a href="https://woocommerce.com/my-account/">Help</a> for WooCommerce.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://community.1and1.com/start-ecommerce-website-wordpress-woocommerce/">Start your eCommerce Website with WordPress and WooCommerce</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://community.1and1.com">1&amp;1 Community</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:79:"https://community.1and1.com/start-ecommerce-website-wordpress-woocommerce/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"0";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:5;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:60:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:5:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:21:"WordPress 4.7 Release";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:42:"https://community.1and1.com/wordpress-4-7/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:50:"https://community.1and1.com/wordpress-4-7/#respond";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Mon, 12 Dec 2016 07:38:18 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:7:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:11:"Information";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:17:"Managed WordPress";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:9:"WordPress";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:3:"4.7";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:4;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:8:"featured";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:5;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:7:"Release";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:6;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:7:"vaughan";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:35:"https://community.1and1.com/?p=9638";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:613:"<p>With WordPress 4.7 „Vaughan“, a great update was released, which, in addition to many improvements, also includes the brand new theme „Twenty Seventeen“.We are already distributing the update to our managed WordPress websites. WordPress standard installations usually also receive the update automatically. If you have disabled the automatic updates for your website, you can install [&#8230;]</p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://community.1and1.com/wordpress-4-7/">WordPress 4.7 Release</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://community.1and1.com">1&amp;1 Community</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:11:"Lucas Radke";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:3575:"<p>With WordPress 4.7 „Vaughan“, a great update was released, which, in addition to many improvements, also includes the brand new theme „Twenty Seventeen“.We are already distributing the update to our managed WordPress websites. WordPress standard installations usually also receive the update automatically.</p>\n<p>If you have disabled the automatic updates for your website, you can install WordPress 4.7 directly from the WordPress admin area. To do this, select <strong>Dashboard</strong> &gt; <strong>Updates</strong> and then <strong>Update Now</strong>.</p>\n<hr />\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a class="promo-button" href="https://mein.1und1.de/APPCenter">Install WordPress</a> oder <a class="promo-button" href="https://my.1and1.com/AllMyApplications">Manage your Websites (1&amp;1 App Center)</a></p>\n<hr />\n<p>WordPress 4.7 Highlights:</p>\n<h3>New Standard Theme Twenty Seventeen</h3>\n<p>Twenty Seventeen surprises by the use of the new video header in combination with parallax scrolling with a dynamic appearance.</p>\n<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-9646" src="https://community.1and1.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/twenty-seventeen-overview.jpg" alt="twenty-seventeen-overview" width="2800" height="1800" srcset="https://community.1and1.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/twenty-seventeen-overview.jpg 2800w, https://community.1and1.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/twenty-seventeen-overview-300x193.jpg 300w, https://community.1and1.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/twenty-seventeen-overview-768x494.jpg 768w, https://community.1and1.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/twenty-seventeen-overview-1024x658.jpg 1024w" sizes="(max-width: 2800px) 100vw, 2800px" />\n<h3>Video Header</h3>\n<p>A video from the media library or from YouTube can now be integrated into the header area.</p>\n<img class="aligncenter wp-image-9612 size-full" src="https://community.1and1.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/wp-twenty-seventteen-start-video-header.png" alt="WordPress Theme Twenty Seventeen with Video Header " width="2880" height="1800" srcset="https://community.1and1.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/wp-twenty-seventteen-start-video-header.png 2880w, https://community.1and1.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/wp-twenty-seventteen-start-video-header-300x188.png 300w, https://community.1and1.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/wp-twenty-seventteen-start-video-header-768x480.png 768w, https://community.1and1.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/wp-twenty-seventteen-start-video-header-1024x640.png 1024w" sizes="(max-width: 2880px) 100vw, 2880px" />\n<h3>Customizer</h3>\n<p>In the customizer, special attention was paid to this update. Websites can be adjusted more quickly and easily to individual needs now.</p>\n<img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-9642" src="https://community.1and1.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/twenty-seventeen-customize.gif" alt="twenty-seventeen-customize" width="640" height="366" />\n<h3>Editor</h3>\n<p>The arrangement of the individual elements in the toolbar has been redesigned to allow even more comfortable working.</p>\n<h3>Sample Content</h3>\n<p>For new websites, sample contents (texts and images) are displayed in the customizer for a better orientation. This will make it easier for new WordPress users to enter the theme .</p>\n<p>Of course, a whole lot of other improvements have been released, on which we will report in detail.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://community.1and1.com/wordpress-4-7/">WordPress 4.7 Release</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://community.1and1.com">1&amp;1 Community</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:47:"https://community.1and1.com/wordpress-4-7/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"0";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:6;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:66:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:5:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:63:"The New SFTP Settings: Access Your Webspace Easily and Securely";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:70:"https://community.1and1.com/the-new-sftp-settings-1and1-control-panel/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:78:"https://community.1and1.com/the-new-sftp-settings-1and1-control-panel/#respond";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Mon, 21 Nov 2016 08:40:56 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:9:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:11:"Information";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:19:"Products & Features";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:4:"WCMS";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:11:"Web Hosting";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:4;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:9:"WordPress";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:5;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:17:"1&1 Control Panel";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:6;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:3:"FTP";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:7;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:11:"highlighted";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:8;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:8:"Webspace";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:35:"https://community.1and1.com/?p=9623";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:442:"<p>SFTP provides you with encrypted and secure access to your webspace and allows you to perform tasks such as installing WordPress manually or creating a backup. </p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://community.1and1.com/the-new-sftp-settings-1and1-control-panel/">The New SFTP Settings: Access Your Webspace Easily and Securely</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://community.1and1.com">1&amp;1 Community</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:16:"Philipp Bellmann";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:4054:"<p>SFTP provides you with encrypted and secure access to your webspace and allows you to perform tasks such as installing WordPress manually or creating a backup. We have revised the FTP settings from the ground up to make SFTP as easy to use as possible:</p>\n<p><strong>All connection data and recommended FTP programs in one place</strong>: User name, assigned directories, FTP server, protocol and port.</p>\n<p><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-9626" src="https://community.1and1.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/ftp-settings-overview.png" alt="ftp-settings-overview" width="2802" height="1194" srcset="https://community.1and1.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/ftp-settings-overview.png 2802w, https://community.1and1.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/ftp-settings-overview-300x128.png 300w, https://community.1and1.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/ftp-settings-overview-768x327.png 768w, https://community.1and1.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/ftp-settings-overview-1024x436.png 1024w" sizes="(max-width: 2802px) 100vw, 2802px" /><br />\n<strong>Set up secure FTP access</strong>: We help you find a secure password. Personal notes allow you to store brief information about a user, e.g. role, tasks, customer or project.</p>\n<img class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-9629" src="https://community.1and1.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/ftp-settings-create-user-1024x587.png" alt="ftp-settings-create-user" width="1024" height="587" srcset="https://community.1and1.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/ftp-settings-create-user-1024x587.png 1024w, https://community.1and1.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/ftp-settings-create-user-300x172.png 300w, https://community.1and1.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/ftp-settings-create-user-768x440.png 768w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" />\n<p><strong>Easily configure FTP programs</strong>: Easily download the appropriate configuration files and import the correct file to your FTP program.</p>\n<img class="aligncenter wp-image-9628 size-full" src="https://community.1and1.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/ftp-settings-create-user-success-e1479717635900.png" alt="ftp-settings-create-user-success" width="2798" height="2181" srcset="https://community.1and1.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/ftp-settings-create-user-success-e1479717635900.png 2798w, https://community.1and1.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/ftp-settings-create-user-success-e1479717635900-300x234.png 300w, https://community.1and1.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/ftp-settings-create-user-success-e1479717635900-768x599.png 768w, https://community.1and1.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/ftp-settings-create-user-success-e1479717635900-1024x798.png 1024w" sizes="(max-width: 2798px) 100vw, 2798px" />\n<p>If you are managing FTP access for a team, you can now send FTP credentials directly to your users by e-mail.</p>\n<p><strong>Download recommended FTP programs</strong>: Our team regularly tests the most popular FTP programs. You can download the best programs directly and securely in the 1&amp;1 Control Panel.</p>\n<img class="aligncenter size-large wp-image-9627" src="https://community.1and1.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/ftp-settings-clients-download-1024x520.png" alt="ftp-settings-clients-download" width="1024" height="520" srcset="https://community.1and1.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/ftp-settings-clients-download-1024x520.png 1024w, https://community.1and1.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/ftp-settings-clients-download-300x152.png 300w, https://community.1and1.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/11/ftp-settings-clients-download-768x390.png 768w" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" />\n<hr />\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a class="promo-button" href="https://mein.1und1.de/ftp-account-overview">Open FTP Settings in the 1&amp;1 Control Panel</a></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://community.1and1.com/the-new-sftp-settings-1and1-control-panel/">The New SFTP Settings: Access Your Webspace Easily and Securely</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://community.1and1.com">1&amp;1 Community</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:75:"https://community.1and1.com/the-new-sftp-settings-1and1-control-panel/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"0";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:7;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:66:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:5:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:56:"Dirty COW Linux Vulnerability: You Are Safe with 1&amp;1";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:44:"https://community.1and1.com/dirty-cow-fixed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:52:"https://community.1and1.com/dirty-cow-fixed/#respond";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Mon, 14 Nov 2016 07:57:15 +0000";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"category";a:9:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:9:"Community";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:4:"WCMS";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:11:"Web Hosting";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:9:"WordPress";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:4;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:11:"highlighted";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:5;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:5:"Linux";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:6;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:5:"patch";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:7;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:8:"Security";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}i:8;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:13:"vulnerability";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:35:"https://community.1and1.com/?p=9616";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:587:"<p>A serious security hole known as Dirty COW was reported in the Linux kernel a few weeks ago. In certain cases, this security hole allows attackers to gain root access to a server and therefore take over the system. Our IT Operations team responded accordingly and updated thousands of servers with millions of customer websites [&#8230;]</p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://community.1and1.com/dirty-cow-fixed/">Dirty COW Linux Vulnerability: You Are Safe with 1&#038;1</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://community.1and1.com">1&amp;1 Community</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:16:"Philipp Bellmann";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:4848:"<p>A serious security hole known as <a href="https://dirtycow.ninja/" target="_blank"><em>Dirty COW</em></a> was reported in the Linux kernel a few weeks ago.</p>\n<p>In certain cases, this security hole allows attackers to gain root access to a server and therefore take over the system.</p>\n<p>Our IT Operations team responded accordingly and updated thousands of servers with millions of customer websites in less than 12 hours.</p>\n<p>All 1&amp;1 web hosting servers are now protected against this security hole.</p>\n<h2>Kernel Patches without Downtime Thanks to Geo-Redundancy</h2>\n<p>For the past several years, we have ensured that all of our customers&#8217; data is saved simultaneously in multiple data centers. If one data center fails, we can therefore switch to a different data center in only a few seconds.</p>\n<p>This redundancy provides your website with maximum availability. It also allows us to install security updates (in this case, kernel patches) without any downtime.</p>\n<p>The Dirty COW kernel patch, for instance, required us to restart all affected servers. This server restart generally takes several minutes and would result in a not insignificant downtime.</p>\n<p>The redundant structure of our servers allowed our IT Operations team to carry out this restart for your websites without downtime in most cases.</p>\n<p><strong>Patch Procedure:</strong></p>\n<p>First, we update the backup server (passive). Then we redirect traffic to this server and update the primary server (active).</p>\n<ol>\n<li>The backup server is updated. Visitors to your website (traffic) are directed to the primary server during this time. All websites remain available.</li>\n<li>Restart, sync and testing of the backup server.<br />\nThe backup server is now secure.</li>\n<li>Traffic is redirected to the backup server.<br />\nNo noticeable downtime.</li>\n<li>The primary server is updated. Traffic is redirected to the backup server during this time. All websites remain available</li>\n<li>Restart, sync and testing of the primary server.<br />\nThe primary server is now secure.</li>\n</ol>\n<p>All servers are now protected against the Dirty COW security hole.</p>\n<h2>Dirty COW: What Is the Problem?</h2>\n<p>The Dirty COW security hole (CVE-2016-5195) is a <em>privilege escalation vulnerability </em>that grants attackers root access to a system. You can find details about the Dirty COW security hole here:</p>\n<p style="text-align: center;"><a class="promo-button" href="https://dirtycow.ninja/">Show Details</a></p>\n<p>Many popular Linux distributions are affected, such as:</p>\n<p>– Red Hat Enterprise Linux 7.x<br />\n– Red Hat Enterprise Linux 6.x<br />\n– Red Hat Enterprise Linux 5.x<br />\n– CentOS Linux 7.x<br />\n– CentOS Linux 6.x<br />\n– CentOS Linux 5.x<br />\n– Debian Linux wheezy<br />\n– Debian Linux jessie<br />\n– Debian Linux stretch<br />\n– Debian Linux sid<br />\n– Ubuntu Linux precise (LTS 12.04)<br />\n– Ubuntu Linux trusty<br />\n– Ubuntu Linux xenial (LTS 16.04)<br />\n– Ubuntu Linux yakkety<br />\n– Ubuntu Linux vivid/ubuntu-core<br />\n– SUSE Linux Enterprise 11 and 12.</p>\n<p><strong>Update Your Private Linux Installation</strong></p>\n<p>If you are using Linux privately, you should take this security hole seriously and update your system as soon as possible.</p>\n<h2>Comment from the Author</h2>\n<p>When I read on Twitter about the Dirty COW security hole one afternoon last week, I said to my wife:</p>\n<p><strong>“Dirty COW vulnerability—sounds like our Linux admins are having a bit of fun!”</strong></p>\n<p>That was the end of the matter for me. We put the kids to bed and then watched the finale of the 6th season of <em>The Walking Dead </em>on Netflix. I didn&#8217;t give it a second thought.</p>\n<p>A week later in a meeting, I learned about the security measures that our IT Operations team implemented in a very short time to protect our servers and our customers&#8217; websites.</p>\n<p>Like most people, I&#8217;m mostly inured to the topic of security. I pay attention to individual issues, but I subconsciously expect that *someone* will solve the problem for me. As a paying customer, that&#8217;s my right, of course. I expect secure web hosting.</p>\n<p>To ensure this security, many security experts and admins regularly work through the night at 1&amp;1 Web Hosting and other providers.</p>\n<p>It might not earn them a medal, but they certainly deserve a small <em>thank you</em> for the next time a security hole is identified in the trade press and I can simply sit at home watching television.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://community.1and1.com/dirty-cow-fixed/">Dirty COW Linux Vulnerability: You Are Safe with 1&#038;1</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://community.1and1.com">1&amp;1 Community</a>.</p>\n";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:36:"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/";a:1:{s:10:"commentRss";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:49:"https://community.1and1.com/dirty-cow-fixed/feed/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/";a:1:{s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1:"0";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}}}i:8;a:6:{s:4:"data";s:54:"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:5:{s:0:"";a:7:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:52:"WordPress 4.7 introduces new theme: Twenty Seventeen";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:80:"https://community.1and1.com/wordpress-4-7-introduces-new-theme